    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Subsystem Internals</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal">Developer-reference notes on individual subsystems: how floating point is approached, how the grain dispatch machinery is generated from tables, and how build-time behavior is gated by compile guards. These complement the operator-lens Architecture &amp; Internals chapter and the register-level deep-dives in 8.3.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">In this section</para>
    <list id="0" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="NotesBox" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">Floating-Point Considerations -- the four formats, the FP-enable gate, FPCR, and the backend strategy.</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">grainFactoryLib -- the table-driven grain codegen.</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">DispatchTables -- the primary and per-kind dispatch tables that bind an opcode to a leaf.</li>
      <li styleclass="NotesBox">CMake Macro Guards -- the build-time options and diagnostic compile guards.</li>
    </list>
